STOP COMPARING YOURSELF TO OTHERS.

To those who compare your own fitness journey to others, especially your trainers, understand that you are more than likely living a very different lifestyle than they are. Trainers and influencers put a lot of time every day into working out, watching their nutrition, etc. They also potentially do it for a living and have gathered a lot of knowledge. They worked up to it and made their own mistakes. instead of comparing yourself and saying that you’ll never get to their level, learn from them. Find out what they do and if what they do suits YOUR goals and YOUR JOURNEY. If it does, great. If not, keep doing your research. Remember, everyone’s body works different. You will never be like them and they may never be what you have the potential to be. So seek out advice and follow what you think is right for you. Comparing yourself can be mentally draining and can therefore affect your physical progress. Instead, take a more positive route by learning from different sources and applying what you think is best for you. You will make mistakes but, just like your trainers, you will learn from your mistakes until you find the right path.

These are normal thoughts that everyone has before committing to something. But ask yourself, what if it works? What if things go perfectly according to plan? What if you succeed? INTERNAL STRUGGLES CAN BE DIFFICULT. 

The last few months have been hard. Not knowing the direction of my fitness journey, losing sight of the things I love most about my career, and just not understanding how I should move forward. Being inconsistent with my workouts, eating food that works against my body’s needs, and taking an overall step back from my health. And you know what? It’s ok. I’m glad. It allowed me to see what I need to do, what my next steps should be and allowed me to see the reality in my situation. Time and time again people say you always have to be motivated, you always have to grind. That’s not true. Sometimes you have to take a step back to take a massive leap forward.

FEELING LOST IS OK.

Not everything in life goes as planned and sometimes things may seem like they are going downhill or even hitting rock bottom while the rest of the world is moving on and forward. It can be downright terrifying to be in a bad position in the current world and rightfully so. But as with everything, you will continue with the flow of life and you too will find your path again. You too will move onto better things and find what’s right for you. Life is never linear. Things are always changing, including your path. These changes lead to growth, expansion of our mind, and lead to a broader sense of self. So tread new surfaces, venture out to new depths, and find the right path for you. And most of all, don’t be afraid - be courageous 

#becourageous #lifecoach #lifelessons #lifegoeson #lifemotivation

Life is a never-ending balancing act, where we must strive to maintain equilibrium between various aspects of our lives. A balanced life is one where we prioritize self-care, work, play, relationships, and personal growth with equal importance, without neglecting any of these areas.

Living a balanced life means making conscious choices and taking intentional actions that support our overall well-being. It means listening to our bodies, minds, and souls and nurturing each of them in a way that feels authentic and fulfilling to us.

Achieving balance is not always easy, and it requires effort, discipline, and commitment. But when we do find that sweet spot, everything just seems to fall into place. We feel energized, fulfilled, and happy, and our relationships, work, and personal growth all thrive.

So, take a step back and evaluate your life. Are you making time for the things that truly matter to you? Are you taking care of your physical, emotional, and mental health? Are you pursuing your passions and dreams?

Remember, balance is not about being perfect or having it all figured out. It's about making progress, one step at a time, towards a life that feels meaningful and fulfilling. So, keep moving forward, stay committed to your goals, and never give up on yourself. You have the power to create the balanced life you deserve. #balancedlife #selfcare #mindbodysoul

Have you ever stopped to think about what it would feel like to hit every single goal you’ve ever set for yourself? Can you imagine the sense of accomplishment, pride, and fulfillment that would come with it?

The truth is, setting goals is the easy part. Staying consistent, motivated, and disciplined through the hardships, obstacles, and moments of weakness and demotivation is what separates the dreamers from the achievers.

When you hit your goals, you’re not just proving to yourself that you’re capable of achieving great things, you’re also building resilience, character, and strength along the way. Every time you push through a tough moment or overcome a challenge, you’re creating a powerful momentum that can carry you through to the finish line.

So I challenge you today to ask yourself: what would it feel like to hit all of your goals? And more importantly, what can you do right now to stay consistent, motivated, and focused on your path towards success?

Remember, success is not a destination, it’s a journey. It’s not about achieving perfection or avoiding failure, it’s about embracing the process, learning from your mistakes, and never giving up on your dreams.

So keep pushing forward, keep striving for greatness, and never forget that anything is possible when you believe in yourself. #fitnessmotivation #nevergiveup #successmindset

In a world where social media can make it feel like everyone is watching your every move, it’s important to remember that the most important work you do is the work you put in when no one is watching. The workouts you do behind closed doors, the healthy choices you make when no one is around to see them, those are the things that really matter.

When you’re working out, it’s easy to get caught up in what other people are doing. You might compare yourself to the person next to you at the gym or feel like you need to post every workout on social media to prove you’re making progress. But the truth is, the only person you should be focusing on is yourself.

When you’re working out and no one is watching, you have the freedom to really focus on yourself. You can tune out distractions and push yourself harder than you might in a crowded gym or a fitness class. You can listen to your body and give it what it needs, whether that’s a challenging workout or a gentle stretch.

So don’t worry about what other people are doing or what they might think of your workouts. Focus on yourself and the progress you’re making behind closed doors. Celebrate the small victories, like being able to do one more rep or holding a plank for a few seconds longer. Remember that the work you’re putting in is what really matters, and the results will come with time.

So keep pushing yourself, keep showing up for yourself, and keep working hard when no one is watching. Because that’s where the real progress is made.

#bethebestyou #focusonyourself #beyourbestself #fitnessmotivation

Discipline is often overlooked as the key ingredient to achieving success, as many people believe that motivation is what drives us towards our goals. However, motivation is a fleeting emotion that can come and go, leaving us feeling lost and unmotivated at times. This is where discipline steps in - it’s what keeps us on track, even when motivation fails us.

Discipline is the foundation of success, as it requires consistency, commitment, and dedication to achieving our goals. It’s about creating healthy habits, staying focused, and pushing through obstacles, even when it’s challenging. With discipline, we can set clear goals, create actionable plans, and stick to them, regardless of how we feel.

Motivation may ignite the fire within us, but discipline keeps it burning. Without discipline, motivation is simply a spark that fades away quickly. When we cultivate discipline, we build the strength to continue even when the going gets tough. We become resilient and adaptable, able to adjust our plans and strategies to overcome any obstacles that come our way.

Discipline is a daily practice that requires intentional effort, but the rewards are immeasurable. By prioritizing discipline over motivation, we create a sustainable path towards success. So, if you’re struggling to stay motivated, focus on cultivating discipline instead. Set realistic goals, create a plan, and commit to taking small steps every day towards achieving your goals. With discipline on your side, anything is possible.

#discipline #successmindset #consistency #strengthtraining

Life is short, and it's important to make the most of every moment. One way to do that is by taking risks and pursuing the things we're truly passionate about. It's easy to get stuck in our comfort zones, but when we step outside of them, that's where the magic happens. Taking risks can be scary, but it's also incredibly rewarding. When we challenge ourselves and push our limits, we grow and learn in ways we never thought possible. We gain confidence, resilience, and a sense of purpose that can help us navigate life's challenges with greater ease.

When we're passionate about something, taking a risk means believing in ourselves and our abilities, and trusting that the journey will be worth it. Whether it's starting a new business, pursuing a new career, or following a dream that's been calling to us for years, taking risks is a healthy and necessary part of growth and development. It means being open to new experiences, embracing uncertainty, and trusting that the universe has our back.

Of course, taking risks doesn't mean we won't experience failure or setbacks along the way. But those experiences are also opportunities to learn and grow, and to become even more resilient and determined in the face of adversity. When we're passionate about something, failure isn't the end, but simply a stepping stone on the path to success.

So if there's something you're passionate about, don't be afraid to take a risk. Trust in yourself, believe in your abilities, and know that the journey will be worth it. Embrace the unknown, and see where your passions can take you. You never know what incredible opportunities and experiences await. #takerisks #followyourpassion #believeinyourself #embracetheunknown #trustthejourney

I TURN 30 TOMORROW (June 17th). 

I always thought it would be scary turning 30. Needing to have everything figured out, making so much money that I could have anything in the world, having a stable career, and starting a family. But that wasn’t my timeline and turning 30 is no longer scary. Normally I’d post an edited, high quality photo. But for my 30th birthday, I’m posting this photo, because in the end, nothing matters but the people that love you, and thanking the universe that you get to spend another day with them. Careers and money will come and go. Life will throw curveballs at you all the time, and material things will wither away with time. But the one constant thing are your family and friends. And from the bottom of my heart, for my 30th, I want to thank all of my family and all of my friends for supporting everything I’ve done up until this moment. It means the world to me. 

#30thbirthday

Hi. It’s been a while. How have you all been? 

I took time off from this page. My mental health was suffering, I was taking a massive leap in my career, and well, I wanted to put my everything into working on what I love to do. This page brought me nothing but stress, sadness and loss of hope. Posts not performing as well as before, setting expectations for myself that were beyond my control, and constantly battling to fight to keep 7 years of work alive with this page. So when it comes to my career, posting to this page was a distraction and hinderance to me having a clear mind and therefore my creativity. I’m proud to say that it was all worth it. And in the healthiest way possible, I’m back.

3 TIPS FOR INTERMITTENT FASTING: 

The most important: EAT A MEAL THAT IS SATIATING BUT ALSO HAS ALL THE NUTRIENTS YOU NEED, ESPECIALLY PROTEIN! 

I like to make sure that I always order food from @sweetgreen so that I’m hitting my macros: healthy carbs, healthy fats, and most importantly, protein. USE MY LINK IN THE BIO TO ORDER YOUR NEXT SWEETGREEN MEAL! 

Another important one: drink tons of water! You need to stay hydrated through the day regardless of the intensity of your fast. We also sometimes confuse hunger with being thirsty or dehydrated. Sometimes you’re not hungry, your body is just trying to tell you that you are hungry. 

And last but not least, TAKE IT SLOW. Don’t set a goal that is unreasonable! Start with an easy fasting schedule and then work your way up.

One thing I’ve learned recently is to always remind yourself why you started to do something you love. At some point in your life, you may start a career path, hobby, etc. and you might become very successful with it. But with that success will come stress, anxiety, the pressure of making an income from it, and you’ll eventually forget that you started to do whatever it is because you genuinely loved it, not because you made money from it. The only reason you were able to make money doing it in the first place is because people saw your genuine love what your craft. So always remember to remind yourself that it’s not about money, fame, etc., it’s about doing what you love. If success comes knocking, great. If not, you still get to do what you love. 

#lifecoach #lifetips #dowhatyoulove #dowhatmakesyouhappy #lovewhatyoudo
